Package cz.cuni.mff.kocur.server

This package implements the HTTP server (using Jetty) and classes that are used to handle the communication with dot2ai addon.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Command
    Interface that represents commands coming out from server or agent.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AgentCommand
    This class represents all the commands any agent can send to the addon.
    AgentCommands
    Class with AgentCommands.
    AgentCommands.Attack
    Class that represents attack command.
    AgentCommands.Buy
    Class that represents the buy command.
    AgentCommands.Cast
    Class that specifies Cast command.
    AgentCommands.GrabAll
    Grab all command.
    AgentCommands.LevelUp
    Levelup command.
    AgentCommands.Move
    Move command.
    AgentCommands.Noop
    Empty command.
    AgentCommands.PickupRune
    Command to pickup a rune with given id.
    AgentCommands.Sell
    Sell command.
    AgentCommands.UseItem
    UseItem command.
    GameCommandsIssuer
    This class can issue in-game commands.
    MapperWrapper
    Wraps the JSON ObjectMapper class.
    RequestArguments
    This class should represent a object, that stores all necessary information about an incoming request.
    RequestChecker
    Class that checks, that the incoming request is correct.
    RequestHandler
    This class extends a AbstractHandler.
    Response
    This class is a helper class, that helps us to create a response to request.
    ServerCommand
    Class that represents a server command.
    ServerCommands
    Class that creates a few commands a server can use.
    ServerCommands.GameCommand
    Class that represents a command, that sends a array of commands to server.
    ServerCommands.Pause
    Class that represents a Pause command.
    ServerCommands.Reset
    Class that represents a reset command.
    ServerCommands.Unpause
    Class that represents a Unpause command.
    ServerManager
    ServerManager is a class that stores a server inside.
    TimeManager
    Class that is supposed to handle time.
